main event: A woman observed a web-like object in the sky while cutting grass in her yard in Columbus, Ohio, on September 13, 1966.
interesting points: The woman described the object as a web-like structure or a parachute., The object was seen moving slowly at treetop height before disappearing., Her dog was barking at the object, indicating its unusual nature., The report mentions that nothing similar had been previously reported., The Air Force suggested that the sighting might have been an optical illusion.
witness description: A woman and her husband were the witnesses, with the woman being the primary observer.
